## 🔢 Key Metrics

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Total Casualties | 417,883 |
| Fatal Casualties | 7,135 (1.7%) |
| Serious Casualties | 59,312 (14.2%) |
| Slight Casualties | 351,436 (84.1%) |
| Casualties by Car | 333,485 (79.8%) |

---

## 📁 Features

- **KPI Cards** — Fatal, Serious, Slight, and Car casualty summaries with % share
- **Monthly Trend** — CY vs PY (2022 vs 2021) line chart for all 12 months
- **Casualties by Vehicle Type** — Car, Truck, Bus, Bike, Agricultural, Other
- **Casualties by Road Type** — Single carriageway, Dual carriageway, Roundabout, One-way, Slip road
- **Casualties by Road Surface** — Dry, Wet, Snow/Ice
- **Casualties by Location** — Urban vs Rural donut chart
- **Casualties by Light Condition** — Daylight vs Dark donut chart
- **Filter Panel** — Slice by Accident Date (Year) and Urban/Rural area

---

## 🛠️ Built With

- Microsoft Excel (Pivot Tables, Pivot Charts)
- Slicers & Timelines for interactive filtering
- Conditional Formatting for KPI indicators
- Custom chart formatting (dark theme)

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

1. Clone or download this repository
2. Open `Road_Accident_Dashboard.xlsx` in Microsoft Excel (2016 or later recommended)
3. Use the **Filter Panel** on the right to slice by year or location type
4. All charts update automatically based on slicer selections

